'From Squeak2.9alpha of 13 June 2000 [latest update: #2426] on 25 June 2000 at 4:01:10 pm'!"Change Set:		169LeaveMeAlone-smaDate:			25 June 2000Author:			Stefan Matthias AustMake a preferences setting to optionally get rid of the ProjectNavigatorMorph.I added it to the #morphic category - see postscript.Arg!! That code code I added to the postscript compiles new preferences methods, I hate self modifying code.  Egal. Sei's drum."!!Preferences class methodsFor: 'help' stamp: 'programmatic 6/25/2000 15:56'!helpMsgsAdditionmorphicshowProjectNavigator	^ #((showProjectNavigator 'If true, then show a nifty project navigator control in the world''s bottom left corner.' ) )! !!Preferences class methodsFor: 'standard preferences' stamp: 'programmatic 6/25/2000 15:56'!showProjectNavigator	^ self valueOfFlag: #showProjectNavigator! !!Preferences class methodsFor: 'initial values' stamp: 'programmatic 6/25/2000 15:56'!initialValuesAdditionmorphicshowProjectNavigator	^ #((showProjectNavigator true (morphic ) ) )! !!Project methodsFor: 'menu messages' stamp: 'sma 6/25/2000 15:59'!finalEnterActions	| navigator |	Preferences showProjectNavigator ifFalse: [^ self].	(world findA: ProjectNavigationMorph) ifNil: [		navigator _ ProjectNavigationMorph new openInWorld.		navigator bottomLeft: world bottomLeft.		"navigator setToAdhereToEdge: #bottomLeft."	].! !"Postscript:"Preferences	addPreference: #showProjectNavigator	category: #morphic	default: true	balloonHelp: 'If true, then show a nifty project navigator control in the world''s bottom left corner.'!